# Everything the automated refresh workflow commits (see .github/workflows/refresh.yml's
# `git add -A -- docs/ data/`) is continuously regenerated by the scheduled GitHub Actions
# run, which always has fresher data than whatever happens to be sitting in a local zip
# download. On a rebase conflict, always take the remote's version of these -- a local
# working copy is never the better source of truth for them, only ever a stale snapshot.
#
# This alone is not enough on its own -- git's built-in "ours" merge driver needs a
# one-time local activation per machine, since .gitattributes can point at a driver
# but can't register one. Run this once:
#   git config merge.ours.driver true
# After that, `git pull --rebase origin main` resolves conflicts on these files
# automatically, with no manual --ours/--theirs step needed ever again.
docs/* merge=ours
data/* merge=ours
